62.6	Kukri	Kukri	The kukri (Devanagari: खुकुरी) (alternatively spelled khukri or khukuri) is a curved Nepalese Knife, similar to the machete, used as both a tool and as a weapon. It is a traditional weapon for Nepalese people, and also a weapon of choice/side arm for all Nepalese including those serving in different armies around the world.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Kukri.jpg/300px-Kukri.jpg
